1 Introduction

This section applies machine learning techniques to uncover patterns in job market data. We use clustering algorithms to group similar job postings and predictive models to forecast salary trends and job categories.

Dataset loaded from: lightcast_job_postings.csv

Columns available: ID, LAST_UPDATED_DATE, LAST_UPDATED_TIMESTAMP, DUPLICATES, POSTED, EXPIRED, DURATION, SOURCE_TYPES, SOURCES, URL...

3 2. K-Means Clustering

3.1 2.1 Determining Optimal Number of Clusters

Use the elbow method to find the optimal number of clusters.

Review the elbow curve to determine optimal K
NoteChoosing Optimal K

Look for the â€œelbowâ€ point where the inertia decrease begins to slow down. This represents the optimal balance between cluster compactness and the number of clusters.

TipUnderstanding PCA Visualization

The scatter plot shows job postings projected onto two principal components. Points of the same color belong to the same cluster, revealing natural groupings in the data.

6 Summary

ImportantMachine Learning Insights

Key findings from ML analysis: - Clustering reveals distinct job market segments based on numerical features - K-Means algorithm successfully groups similar job postings - PCA visualization helps understand cluster separation - Predictive models can estimate salaries based on job characteristics

Recommendations: - Target jobs in clusters with favorable characteristics - Focus on features with high importance for salary optimization - Use cluster insights to refine job search strategy
